FBIS4-40151 "drsov115_a_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 14 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Duma Speaker Shares Yeltsin Views on DPRK Sanctions Duma Speaker Shares Yeltsin Views on DPRK Sanctions LD1406142194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1332 GMT 14 Jun 94 LD1406142194 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] State Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin fully shares President Yeltsin's view that international sanctions against North Korea should be coordinated with UN members and imposed gradually. As the chairman of the State Duma Defense Committee, Sergey Yushenkov, told Interfax, Rybkin expressed this agreement with Yeltsin's view on Tuesday, when receiving a parliamentary delegation from Britain. Led by the chairman of the Standing Commission for Defense of the House of Commons, Nicholas Bonsor, the delegation took part in Tuesday's round-table conference on collective security in Europe held at the lower chamber of Russia's parliament. Interfax's correspondent reports that on Wednesday British MPs intend to visit Russia's Defense Ministry, Institute for Strategic Studies and a military unit. Thursday evening they will leave for Kiev.
